messages.content:
{
    "thought_on_cooking_style": "The cooking style presented in the given recipes emphasizes simplicity and flavor. It involves basic techniques such as sauting, baking, and seasoning to enhance the natural flavors of the ingredients. The use of garlic is prominent, providing a robust flavor profile to the chicken dishes. The recipes also show a preference for cooking in their own juices or with minimal added fat, allowing the ingredients' natural flavors to shine through. This approach is both health-conscious and flavor-focused.",
    "thought_on_recipe": "For the garlic chicken recipe, I will draw inspiration from the given examples, focusing on creating a dish that is simple to prepare, yet rich in flavor. The recipe will involve pan-searing and oven-finishing to achieve a well-browned and crispy exterior while maintaining a juicy interior. Garlic will be used both in the marinade and as a component of the sauce to ensure the flavor permeates the chicken. The use of fresh herbs will complement the garlic and add depth to the dish.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title": "Oven-Roasted Garlic Herb Chicken",
            "description": "This recipe features a succulent chicken breast marinated in a garlic herb mixture, pan-seared to golden perfection, and finished in the oven. The dish is accompanied by a rich garlic-infused sauce, making it a hearty and aromatic meal.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Prepare the marinade by finely mincing 4 cloves of garlic and mixing them with 1 tablespoon of olive oil, 1 teaspoon of chopped fresh rosemary, 1 teaspoon of chopped fresh thyme, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Place two chicken breasts in a bowl and coat them thoroughly with the marinade. Let them sit for at least 30 minutes to absorb the flavors."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Heat a cast-iron skillet or oven-proof pan over medium-high heat. Once hot, place the marinated chicken breasts skin side down and sear for about 4 minutes until the skin is golden and crispy."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Flip the chicken breasts over and cook for another 2 minutes."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and roast the chicken for 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 165 degrees Fahrenheit."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the chicken is roasting, prepare the garlic sauce by finely chopping 2 additional cloves of garlic. In a small saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat and saut the garlic until fragrant."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Add 1/2 cup of chicken broth to the saucepan, bring to a simmer, and reduce by half. Season with salt and pepper to taste."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Once the chicken is done, let it rest for a few minutes before slicing. Serve the chicken with the garlic sauce drizzled on top."
                }
            ]
        }
}
